Argentine Stocks: Banco Macro, BBVA, Petrobras Argentina Rise

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-07-26T16:48:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-26/argentine-stocks-banco-macro-bbva-petrobras-argentina-rise.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:41 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 0.8 percent to 3,357.52.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)  ,  Argentina ’s largest lender by
market value, gained 2 percent to 15.30 pesos. The price of
Argentine sovereign bonds rose today, which signals higher value
for banks’ fixed-income holdings.  BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN)  , a unit of  Spain ’s Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA,
climbed 1.1 percent to 13.65 pesos.   Petrobras Argentina (PESA AF), the local unit of  Brazil ’s
state-controlled oil company Petroleo Brasileiro SA, rose 1.6
percent to 8.25 pesos. Petrobras said its plan to more than
double output will boost  cash flow  and eliminate the need to tap
debt markets after about 10 years.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in  Buenos Aires  at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  